This creates a new branch named â€œmy-feature-branchâ€ and switches to it.
From GitHub Web Interface:
Go to your repository on GitHub.
Click the â€œBranchâ€ dropdown and type a new branch name. Hit Enter.
VoilÃ ! Your branch is born.
Making Changes (Code Gardening)
Work on Your Branch:
Edit files, add features, fix bugsâ€”whatever your heart desires.
Commit your changes:
